  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Builder<PhoneNumberTranslator>, Parent<SenderNumberBuilder>

    public class SenderNumberFormatBuilder
extends AbstractParent<SenderNumberBuilder>
implements Builder<PhoneNumberTranslator>
    Defines which standard conversions may be applied on the phone number to convert it from a PhoneNumber to an AddressedPhoneNumber.

    • Method Detail

      • alphanumericCode

        public SenderNumberFormatBuilder alphanumericCode(Boolean enable)
        Enable/disable alphanumeric code conversion: if the sender address is alphanumeric (contains both letters and numbers) or non-numeric, TON is set to 5 and NPI to 0.

        The value set using this method takes precedence over any property and default value configured using alphanumericCode(). 

         .alphanumericCode(false)
 .alphanumericCode()
   .properties("${custom.property.high-priority}", "${custom.property.low-priority}")
   .defaultValue(true)
 
         .alphanumericCode(false)
 .alphanumericCode()
   .properties("${custom.property.high-priority}", "${custom.property.low-priority}")
   .defaultValue(true)
        In both cases, alphanumericCode(false) is used.

        If this method is called several times, only the last value is used.

        If null value is set, it is like not setting a value at all. The property/default value configuration is applied.

        Parameters:
        enable - enable or disable alphanumeric code convertion
        Returns:
        this instance for fluent chaining

      • alphanumericCode

        public ConfigurationValueBuilder<SenderNumberFormatBuilder,Boolean> alphanumericCode()
        Enable/disable alphanumeric code conversion: if the sender address is alphanumeric (contains both letters and numbers) or non-numeric, TON is set to 5 and NPI to 0.

        This method is mainly used by Configurers to register some property keys and/or a default value. The aim is to let developer be able to externalize its configuration (using system properties, configuration file or anything else). If the developer doesn't configure any value for the registered properties, the default value is used (if set). 

         .alphanumericCode()
   .properties("${custom.property.high-priority}", "${custom.property.low-priority}")
   .defaultValue(true)

        Non-null value set using alphanumericCode(Boolean) takes precedence over property values and default value. 

         .alphanumericCode(true)
 .alphanumericCode()
   .properties("${custom.property.high-priority}", "${custom.property.low-priority}")
   .defaultValue(true)
        The value true is used regardless of the value of the properties and default value.

        See ConfigurationValueBuilder for more information.

        Returns:
        the builder to configure property keys/default value

      • shortCode

        public SenderNumberFormatBuilder shortCode(Boolean enable)
        Enable/disable short code conversion: if the sender address is a short code, TON is set to 3, and NPI is set to 0. A number is considered to be a short code if the length of the number is 5 digits or less.

        The value set using this method takes precedence over any property and default value configured using shortCode(). 

         .shortCode(false)
 .shortCode()
   .properties("${custom.property.high-priority}", "${custom.property.low-priority}")
   .defaultValue(true)
 
         .shortCode(false)
 .shortCode()
   .properties("${custom.property.high-priority}", "${custom.property.low-priority}")
   .defaultValue(true)
        In both cases, shortCode(false) is used.

        If this method is called several times, only the last value is used.

        If null value is set, it is like not setting a value at all. The property/default value configuration is applied.

        Parameters:
        enable - enable or disable short code conversion
        Returns:
        this instance for fluent chaining
